      • handleNonReference

        public <T> R handleNonReference(Bound<T> term)
        Handle a non-reference value in this visitor.

        Visitors that require references and not terms can use this method to return a default value for expressions with non-references. The default implementation will throw a validation exception because the non-reference is not supported.

        Type Parameters:
        T - a Java return type
        Parameters:
        term - a non-reference bound expression
        Returns:
        a return value for the visitor
